http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/Swachh-mission-to-be-intensified/article13975891.ece

Kozhikode Corporation will intensify its activities in connection with the Swachh Bharat Mission of the Centre, Mayor V.K.C. Mammed Koya, has said.He said here on Friday that priority would be given to provide toilet facilities in all households in the city. A preliminary survey carried out by the Kudumbasree Mission between July 29 and September 4, 2015 had found out that 911 houses did not have household latrines. Another 594 toilets were either in a dilapidated or unusable condition.The Mayor said that 98 per cent of the State had individual household toilets. However, the objective was to make it 100 per cent by March 31, 2016.The civic body had taken steps to identify the beneficiaries in all the 75 wards of the Corporation.The Akshaya Kendras had incorporated the details of their databank.However, the server which was located in Chennai got damaged following the recent floods in that city. Now steps are being taken to retrieve the databank.Mr. Koya said that the health wing of the Corporation had also identified the locations in slum areas and colonies in the city where public toilets should be established. The aim was to construct the toilets with the participation of the private sector.Community toilets will be constructed at five places and public toilets at 14 places as per the survey.This would be done shortly, he said.Besides, the civic body will give utmost priority to solid waste management in the city. A detailed project would be prepared to construct a modern treatment plant and purchase equipment and vehicles to transport garbage.Kozhikode is one of the three cities in the State that have been included in the Swachh Bharat Mission. The others are Kochi and Thiruvananthapuram.The project is being implemented in 82 cities across different States in the country.